==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symptomatical
<hw>Symp`tom*at"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>symptomatique</ets>, Gr. <?/ causal.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or
pertaining to symptoms; happening in concurrence with something; being a
symptom; indicating the existence of something else.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Symptomatic</qex> of a shallow understanding and an unamiable
temper.</q> <rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>According to symptoms; <as>as, a
<ex>symptomatical</ex> classification of diseases</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Symp`tom*at"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symptomatology</ent>⟦br⟧
